821:## Task 3: Capture trusted portal asset-route failures, keep the Plex glyph fix durable, and harden Cloudflare Tunnel route matching on `main`, outcome: success
825:- rollout_summaries/2026-06-30T10-52-06-eTrc-plex_font_routing_cloudflare_regex_fix.md (cwd=/Users/jamesto/Coding/mini-hub, rollout_path=/Users/jamesto/.codex/sessions/2026/06/30/rollout-2026-06-30T11-52-06-019f1828-5c14-7923-90c1-97e2fcfbc3f2.jsonl, updated_at=2026-07-02T00:57:47+00:00, thread_id=019f1828-5c14-7923-90c1-97e2fcfbc3f2, Cloudflare Tunnel regex-path fix for Plex fonts and Scrypted endpoint assets plus `main` commit/push cleanup)
831:- trusted portal asset route, Plex, square placeholder glyphs, Caddy, nosniff, font/woff, font/woff2, cloudflared, regex path matching, /web/static/, /endpoint/, docs/solutions, CONCEPTS.md, AGENTS.md, verify-trusted-entrance.py, verify-public-ingress.sh, main branch, .spk, macm4 trusted entrance
858:- The durable trusted-portal lesson is broader than one Plex bug: browser-visible breakage can come from root-relative asset namespaces such as fonts, icons, manifests, locale JSON, and endpoint shells even when the main page loads. `docs/solutions/` is now the learning store for that pattern, `CONCEPTS.md` holds the ingress vocabulary, and `AGENTS.md` explicitly points future agents at both. [Task 3]
860:- The verifier hardening that should survive is dynamic discovery: parse current Plex Web CSS to find the active `.woff` / `.woff2` assets instead of pinning one hash, then validate the MIME type on both trusted entrance origins. [Task 3]
861:- The newer routing lesson that superseded a too-narrow Caddy-only diagnosis was: Cloudflare Tunnel managed `path` fields behave like regular expressions, so unanchored paths such as `/s/*` can accidentally match the `s` inside Plex `/web/static/...` and send font requests to the wrong origin. Anchor the route expressions and explicitly cover Scrypted `/endpoint/...` assets. [Task 3]
871:- Symptom: a trusted portal page loads but fonts/icons/locale assets still break. Cause: the route fix covered only the landing page, not the browser-loaded asset namespace. Fix: verify asset requests explicitly and document the broader portal-asset-route pattern in `docs/solutions/` so future fixes do not stop too early. [Task 3]
872:- Symptom: Plex icons turn into square placeholder glyphs only through the trusted entrance. Cause: browser `nosniff` rejects font assets served as the wrong MIME through the proxy path. Fix: rewrite the response MIME type in Caddy rather than loosening headers or changing Plex itself. [Task 3]
873:- Symptom: a quick header override produces duplicate `Content-Type` headers, or future regressions slip past after Plex asset hashes change. Cause: adding a second header and hard-coding one hashed asset path are both brittle. Fix: use response-header replacement semantics and dynamic CSS-based asset discovery in the verifier. [Task 3]
874:- Symptom: Plex fonts or Scrypted endpoint assets still fail even after the origin service itself looks healthy. Cause: Cloudflare Tunnel regex-style path matching is steering the request to the wrong origin before Caddy/app behavior even matters. Fix: inspect the live managed tunnel config, anchor the path expressions, and verify route ownership with `cloudflared tunnel --config ... ingress rule ...` before changing the app. [Task 3]
